OBI:0200179.definition:
A class prediction objective (sometimes called supervised classification) is a data transformation objective where the aim is to create a predictor from training data through a machine learning technique. The training data consist of pairs of objects (typically vectors of attributes) and
class labels for these objects. The resulting predictor can be used to attach class labels to any valid novel input object. Depending on usage, the prediction can be definite or probabilistic. A classification is learned from the training data and can then be tested on test data.
OBI:0200179.label: class prediction objective

OBI:0200178.definition: A class discovery objective (sometimes called unsupervised classification) is a data transformation objective where the aim is to organize input data  (typically vectors of attributes) into classes, where the number of classes and their specifications are not known a priori. Depending on usage, the class assignment can be definite or probabilistic.
OBI:0200178.label: class discovery objective

OBI:0200175.definition: A class discovery data transformation (sometimes called unsupervised classification) is a data transformation that has objective class discovery.

CHEBI:33284.label: nutrient

CHEBI:33285.label: heteroorganic entity

CHEBI:33286.definition: An agrochemical is a substance that is used in agriculture or horticulture.
CHEBI:33286.label: agrochemical

CHEBI:33287.definition: A fertilizer is any substance that is added to soil or water to assist the growth of plants.
CHEBI:33287.label: fertilizer

PO:0025028.definition: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that is part of a plant embryo (PO:0009009).
PO:0025028.label: embryo plant cell

PO:0025029.definition: A plant axis (PO:0025004) that is part of a shoot system (PO:0009006).
PO:0025029.label: shoot axis

ENVO:00000106.definition: An area in which grasses (Graminae) are a significant component of the vegetation.
ENVO:00000106.label: grassland

ENVO:00002249.definition: Phaeozems accommodate soils of relatively wet grassland and forest regions in moderately continental climates. Phaeozems are much like Chernozems and Kastanozems but are leached more intensively. Consequently, they have dark, humus rich surface horizons that, in comparison with Chernozems and Kastanozems, are less rich in bases. Phaeozems may or may not have secondary carbonates but have a high base saturation in the upper metre of the soil.
ENVO:00002249.label: phaeozem

ENVO:00002248.definition: Luvisols are soils that have a higher clay content in the subsoil than in the topsoil as a result of pedogenetic processes (especially clay migration) leading to an argic subsoil horizon. Luvisols have high-activity clays throughout the argic horizon and a high base saturation at certain depths.
ENVO:00002248.label: luvisol

ENVO:00002247.definition: Nitisols are deep, well-drained, red, tropical soils with diffuse horizon boundaries and a subsurface horizon with more than 30 percent clay and moderate to strong angular blocky structure elements that easily fall apart into characteristic shiny, polyhedric (nutty) elements. Weathering is relatively advanced but Nitisols are far more productive than most other red, tropical soils.
ENVO:00002247.label: nitisol

ENVO:00002246.definition: Ferralsols represent the classical, deeply weathered, red or yellow soils of the humid tropics. These soils have diffuse horizon boundaries, a clay assemblage dominated by low-activity clays (mainly kaolinite) and a high content of sesquioxides.
ENVO:00002246.label: ferralsol

ENVO:00002245.definition: Gypsisols are soils with substantial secondary accumulation of gypsum (calcium sulfate). These soils are found in the driest parts of the arid climate zone.
ENVO:00002245.label: gypsisol

ENVO:00002244.definition: Gleysols are wetland soils that, unless drained, are saturated with groundwater for long enough periods to develop a characteristic gleyic colour pattern. This pattern is essentially made up of reddish, brownish or yellowish colours at ped surfaces and/or in the upper soil layer or layers, in combination with greyish/bluish colours inside the peds and/or deeper in the soil.
ENVO:00002244.label: gleysol

ENVO:00002243.definition: Histosols comprise soils formed in organic material. These vary from soils developed in predominantly moss peat in boreal, arctic and subarctic regions, via moss peat, reeds/ sedge peat (fen) and forest peat in temperate regions to mangrove peat and swamp forest peat in the humid tropics. Histosols are found at all altitudes, but the vast majority occurs in lowlands.
ENVO:00002243.label: histosol

ENVO:00002240.definition: Kastanozems are dry grassland soils, among them the zonal soils of the short-grass steppe belt, south of the Eurasian tall-grass steppe belt with Chernozems. Kastanozems have a similar profile to that of Chernozems but the humus-rich surface horizon is thinner and not as dark as that of the Chernozems and they show more prominent accumulation of secondary carbonates.
ENVO:00002240.label: kastanozem

CHEBI:64049.definition: A food additive that is used to change or otherwise control the acidity or alkalinity of foods. They may be acids, bases, neutralising agents or buffering agents.
CHEBI:64049.label: food acidity regulator

CHEBI:64047.definition: Any substance which is added to food to preserve or enhance its flavour and/or appearance.
CHEBI:64047.label: food additive

OBI:0002243.definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of renal cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.
OBI:0002243.label: pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition

PATO:0001355.definition: A shape quality that obtains by virtue of the bearer having inward facing edges; having a surface or boundary that curves or bulges outward, as the exterior of a sphere.
PATO:0001355.label: convex

PATO:0001353.definition: A density quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of some influence exerted by the bearer's mass on a given volume.
PATO:0001353.label: volumetric density

PATO:0001352.definition: A density quality which is equal to the mass exerting an influence on a one-dimensional object.
PATO:0001352.label: linear density

PATO:0001351.definition: A density quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of some influence exerted by the bearer's mass on a given area.
PATO:0001351.label: area density

AGRO:00000112.definition: A planned process in which a liming material is applied to soil to reduce acidity.
AGRO:00000112.label: liming process

AGRO:00000113.definition: Seed soaked in water until the physical process of germination, the penetration of the root though the seed coat, has occurred.
AGRO:00000113.label: pregerminated seed

AGRO:00000111.label: mulching process

AGRO:00000116.definition: Organism used to pull agricultural implements.
AGRO:00000116.label: draft animal

AGRO:00000114.definition: Piece of a plant, often piece of the stem or root, that is used for vegetative propagation.
AGRO:00000114.label: plant cutting

AGRO:00000115.definition: A shoot of a perennial plant.
AGRO:00000115.label: ratoon

PATO:0002326.definition: An orientation inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's placement at an angle.
PATO:0002326.label: angle

ENVO:00000508.definition: A step-like feature between higher and lower ground: a relatively flat or gently inclined shelf of earth, backed and fronted by steep slopes or manmade detaining walls.
ENVO:00000508.label: terrace

PATO:0000069.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the whether the bearer differs from normal or average.
PATO:0000069.label: deviation(from_normal)

ENVO:00000501.definition: The portion of the ground surface which lies below water.
ENVO:00000501.label: bed

ENVO:01000772.definition: An area which is outside of a town, city, or urban area. Rural areas are primarily used for agriculture or pastoralism and may contain rural settlements.
ENVO:01000772.label: rural area

PATO:0001585.definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to transmit of an entity through a medium.
PATO:0001585.label: conductivity

CHEBI:77974.definition: A food additive that is a (generally inert) gas which is used to envelop foodstuffs during packing and so protect them from unwanted chemical reactions such as food spoilage or oxidation during subsequent transport and storage. CHEBI:77974.label: food packaging gas

ENVO:00000341.definition: A piece of rock that is two millimeters (2mm) in its largest dimension (about 1/12 of an inch) and no more than 75 millimeters (about 3 inches).

ENVO:00000433.definition: A terrace associated with a kame.
ENVO:00000433.label: kame terrace

OBI:0001293.definition: A study design in which the pathological condition of a part, organ, or system of an organism is studied. The etiology may be from infection, genetic defect, or environmental stress.
OBI:0001293.label: disease state design

ENVO:00000230.definition: A wetland associated with the part of the land adjoining or near a sea or ocean.
ENVO:00000230.label: coastal wetland

ENVO:00000233.definition: A wetland that features permanent inundation of large areas of land by shallow bodies of water, generally with a substantial number of hummocks, or dry-land protrusions.
ENVO:00000233.label: swamp

OBI:0000749.definition: A CART (classification and regression trees) is a data transformation method for producing a classification or regression model with a tree-based structure.
OBI:0000749.label: CART

PATO:0000984.definition: A porosity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being capable of admitting the passage of gas or liquid through pores or interstices.
PATO:0000984.label: porous

IAO:0000015.label: information carrier

ENVO:00003074.label: manufactured product

ENVO:01001010.definition: A meteor which is primarily composed of water.

A histogram is a report graph which is a statistical description of a
distribution in terms of occurrence frequencies of different event classes.
IAO:0000179.label: histogram

CHEBI:35276.label: ammonium compound

CHEBI:35274.definition: Ammonium, NH4(+), and derivatives formed by substitution by univalent groups.
CHEBI:35274.label: ammonium ion

AGRO:00000346.definition: A complication with a person or a group of people working on the experiement.
AGRO:00000346.label: personel complication

AGRO:00000345.definition: A complication with the equipement used during the experiment.
AGRO:00000345.label: equipement complication

AGRO:00000344.definition: Unexpected event arrived during the experiment.

AGRO:00000342.label: experimental constraint

AGRO:00000341.definition: A factor of an experiment is a controlled independent variable; a variable whose levels are set by the experimenter. A factor is a general type or category of treatments. Different treatments constitute different levels of a factor.
AGRO:00000341.label: experimental factor

ENVO:00000142.definition: The sloping margin of a stream, serving to confine it to its natural channel.
ENVO:00000142.label: stream bank

OBI:0000947.definition: is a role which inheres in a person or organization and is realized in in a planned process which provides access to training, materials or execution of protocols for an organization or person
OBI:0000947.label: service provider role

PO:0007033.definition: A plant structure development stage (PO:0009012) that has as primary participant a whole plant (PO:0000003).
PO:0007033.label: whole plant development stage

CHEBI:35604.label: carbon oxoanion

PATO:0002005.definition: Surface shape that refers to the inward or outward curvature of the surface.
PATO:0002005.label: concavity

AGRO:00000291.definition: Assess visually the percentage of soil covered by environmental material.
AGRO:00000291.label: soil coverage visual assessment protocol

AGRO:00000290.definition: Protocol that describes how to measure the percentage of soil coverage by environmental material like mulch or crop residue.
AGRO:00000290.label: soil coverage by environmental material measurement protocol

AGRO:00000297.label: incorporation percentage measurement using GIS

AGRO:00000298.definition: Measure the percentage of environmental material that has been buried into soil by counting the environmental material using quadrat, rope with knots or other devices befor and after the incorporation process.
AGRO:00000298.label: incorporation percentage manual measurement

ENVO:00002252.definition: Solonchaks are soils that have a high concentration of soluble salts at some time in the year. Solonchaks are largely confined to the arid and semi-arid climate zones and to coastal regions in all climates.
ENVO:00002252.label: solonchak

ENVO:00002254.definition: A soil in which there is a high content of expansive clay known as montmorillonite that forms deep cracks in drier seasons or years. Alternate shrinking and swelling causes self-mulching, where the soil material consistently mixes itself, causing vertisols to have an extremely deep A horizon and no B horizon.
ENVO:00002254.label: vertisol

ENVO:00002255.definition: Solonetz are soils with a dense, strongly structured, clayey subsurface horizon that has a high proportion of adsorbed Na and/or Mg ions. Solonetz that contain free soda (Na2CO3) are strongly alkaline (field pH > 8.5).
ENVO:00002255.label: solonetz

ENVO:00002256.definition: Regosols form a taxonomic remnant group containing all soils that could not be accommodated in any of the other RSGs. In practice, Regosols are very weakly developed mineral soils in unconsolidated materials that do not have a mollic or umbric horizon, are not very shallow or very rich in gravels (Leptosols), sandy (Arenosols) or with fluvic materials (Fluvisols). Regosols are extensive in eroding lands, particularly in arid and semi-arid areas and in mountainous terrain.
ENVO:00002256.label: regosol

ENVO:00002257.definition: Podzols are soils with a typically ash-grey upper subsurface horizon, bleached by loss of organic matter and iron oxides, on top of a dark accumulation horizon with brown, reddish or black illuviated humus and/or reddish Fe compounds. Podzols occur in humid areas in the boreal and temperate zones and locally also in the tropics.
ENVO:00002257.label: podzol

ENVO:01000560.definition: Charcoal is a light, black residue, consisting of carbon and any remaining ash, obtained by removing water and other volatile constituents from animal and vegetation substances. Charcoal is usually produced by slow pyrolysis, the heating of wood or other substances in the absence of oxygen.
ENVO:01000560.label: charcoal

CHEBI:64709.definition: Any organic molecular entity that is acidic and contains carbon in covalent linkage.
CHEBI:64709.label: organic acid

CHEBI:64708.definition: An organic molecular entity containing a single carbon atom (C1).
CHEBI:64708.label: one-carbon compound

PATO:0001025.definition: A physical quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's amount of force per unit area it exerts.
PATO:0001025.label: pressure

OBI:0002256.definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.
OBI:0002256.label: pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition

AGRO:00000129.definition: An implement that cut, lift and reverse soil with a cutting depth of approximately 15 cm.
AGRO:00000129.label: mouldboard plough

AGRO:00000128.definition: An implement that consists of many carbon steel or boron discs, which have many varying concavities and disc blade sizes and spacing and which are arranged into two or four sections. It is used to till the soil where crops are to be planted. It is also used to chop up unwanted weeds or crop remainders.
AGRO:00000128.label: disk harrow

AGRO:00000127.definition: A roller armed with blunt spikes for dragging over newly plowed land to break the clods and render it fit for seeding.
AGRO:00000127.label: clod crusher

AGRO:00000126.definition: A tractor with two axles. Agricultural implements may be towed behind or mounted on the tractor, and the tractor may also provide a source of power if the implement is mechanized.
AGRO:00000126.label: two-axle tractor

AGRO:00000125.definition: A tractor with one axle, self-powered and self-propelled. The operator usually walks behind it or rides the implement being towed.
AGRO:00000125.label: single-axle tractor

AGRO:00000124.definition: A mobile machine specifically designed to deliver a high tractive effort at slow speeds, and mainly used for the purposes of hauling a trailer or machinery used in agriculture or construction.
AGRO:00000124.label: tractor

CHEBI:16199.definition: A carbonyl group with two C-bound amine groups.
CHEBI:16199.label: urea

PATO:0000161.definition: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's occurrence per unit time.
PATO:0000161.label: rate

CHEBI:33579.definition: A molecular entity containing one or more atoms from any of groups 1, 2, 13, 14, 15, 16, 17, and 18 of the periodic table.
CHEBI:33579.label: main group molecular entity

IAO:0000572.definition: a planned process in which a document is created or added to by including the specified input in it.
IAO:0000572.label: documenting

PATO:0001759.definition: A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's containing granules.
PATO:0001759.label: granular

PATO:0001757.definition: A conductivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to convey electricity.
PATO:0001757.label: electrical conductivity

AGRO:00000426.definition: A planned process in which grazing animals on pasture are managed by humans.
AGRO:00000426.label: regulation of grazing

ENVO:01000703.definition: Hydrological precipitation is a process during which any product of the condensation of atmospheric water vapour is pulled to the planetary surface by gravity.
ENVO:01000703.label: hydrological precipitation process

ENVO:01000705.definition: Soil degradation is a process which results in a change in soil health status resulting in a diminished capacity of the ecosystem in which the soil occurs to provide goods and services for its  beneficiaries.
ENVO:01000705.label: soil degradation

ENVO:01000706.definition: Soil erosion is a process in which exogenic processes remove soil from one location on the Earth's crust and transport it to another location where it is deposited.
ENVO:01000706.label: soil erosion

PATO:0001591.definition: A surface shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a degree of bending.
PATO:0001591.label: curvature

PATO:0001595.definition: A 1-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's downward or backward or inward dimenision.
PATO:0001595.label: depth

CHEBI:25367.definition: Any polyatomic entity that is an electrically neutral entity consisting of more than one atom.
CHEBI:25367.label: molecule

CHEBI:25362.definition: A molecule all atoms of which have the same atomic number.
CHEBI:25362.label: elemental molecule

OBI:0600007.definition: A process by which a substance is intentionally given to an organism resulting in exposure of the organism to that substance.
OBI:0600007.label: administering substance in vivo

AGRO:00000423.definition: Total quantity of fertilizer applied in a given surface area during a cropping season.
AGRO:00000423.label: fertilizer area density over a cropping season

AGRO:00000420.definition: Vertical arrangement of plants in a field.
AGRO:00000420.label: column

ENVO:01000018.definition: Gravel is an environmental material which is composed of pieces of rock that are at least two millimeters (2mm) in its largest dimension and no more than 75 millimeters.
ENVO:01000018.label: gravel

ENVO:01000017.definition: A naturally occurring granular material composed of finely divided rock and mineral particles.
ENVO:01000017.label: sand

ENVO:01000016.definition: Silt is granular material of a size somewhere between sand and clay whose mineral origin is quartz and feldspar.
ENVO:01000016.label: silt

OBI:0001933.definition: An information content entity that specifies a value within a classification scheme or on a quantitative scale.
OBI:0001933.label: value specification

OBI:0001930.definition: A value specification that is specifies one category out of a fixed number of nominal categories
OBI:0001930.label: categorical value specification

OBI:0001931.definition: A value specification that consists of two parts: a numeral and a unit label
OBI:0001931.label: scalar value specification

PATO:0001687.definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's vertical distance of a point above or below a reference surface.
PATO:0001687.label: elevation

CHEBI:25212.definition: Any intermediate or product resulting from metabolism. The term 'metabolite' subsumes the classes commonly known as primary and secondary metabolites.
CHEBI:25212.label: metabolite

PATO:0001689.definition: An elevation which is relatively low.
PATO:0001689.label: decreased elevation

PATO:0001688.definition: An elevation which is relatively high.
PATO:0001688.label: increased elevation

ENVO:00000393.definition: A large sea or ocean inlet larger than a bay, deeper than a bight, wider than a fjord, or it may identify a narrow sea or ocean channel between two bodies of land.
ENVO:00000393.label: sound

CHEBI:23117.definition: A halogen molecular entity containing one or more atoms of chlorine.
CHEBI:23117.label: chlorine molecular entity

OBI:0000648.definition: A data set that is produced as the output of a class discovery data transformation and consists of a data set with assigned discovered class labels.
OBI:0000648.label: clustered data set

ENVO:00000395.definition: The physical confine of a river, slough or ocean strait consisting of a bed and banks.
ENVO:00000395.label: channel of a watercourse

ENVO:01000375.definition: A tropical marine condition is a tropical condition in which the ocean strongly influences the climate and a wet and dry season occur.
ENVO:01000375.label: tropical marine condition

ENVO:01000376.definition: A semi-evergreen forest is a forest which undergoes a long dry season and, as a consequence, has a two-storey layer structure,  a dry canopy, a leaf litter layer that only decays during moist periods trees with very small leaves or which shed their leaves to conserve water and which flower during the dry season and grow during the wet season.
ENVO:01000376.label: tropical marine semi-evergreen forest

ENVO:00000248.definition: A valley that contains, or contained, a glacier and was formed by glacial activity. Typically U-shaped in cross-section.
ENVO:00000248.label: glacial valley

PATO:0000407.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a horizontal surface without a slope, tilt, or curvature.
PATO:0000407.label: flat

ENVO:00000243.definition: A wetland whose water that contains low concentrations of salts.
ENVO:00000243.label: freshwater wetland

ENVO:00000247.definition: An opening, or rupture, in the Earth's surface or crust, which allows hot, molten rock, ash and gases to escape from deep below the surface.
ENVO:00000247.label: volcano

ENVO:01000179.definition: A desert biome is a terrestrial biome which loses more liquid water by evapotranspiration than is supplied by precipitation and includes communities adapted to these conditions.
ENVO:01000179.label: desert biome

PATO:0000970.definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being permeated or pervaded by a gas or liquid (as by osmosis or diffusion).
PATO:0000970.label: permeability

OBI:0200041.definition: A k-means clustering is a data transformation which achieves a class discovery or partitioning objective, which takes as input a collection of objects (represented as points in multidimensional space) and which partitions them into a specified number k of clusters. The algorithm attempts to find the centers of natural clusters in the data. The most common form of the algorithm starts by partitioning the input points into k initial sets, either at random or using some heuristic data. It then calculates the mean point, or centroid, of each set. It constructs a new partition by associating each point with the closest centroid. Then the centroids are recalculated for the new clusters, and the algorithm repeated by alternate applications of these two steps until convergence, which is obtained when the points no longer switch clusters (or alternatively centroids are no longer changed).
OBI:0200041.label: k-means clustering

OBI:0002298.label: pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition

ENVO:00000123.definition: A geographical region whose affairs and population are administered by an authority.
ENVO:00000123.label: political entity

PATO:0000146.definition: A physical quality of the thermal energy of a system.
PATO:0000146.label: temperature

PATO:0000141.definition: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's relative position, shape, arrangements and connectivity of an organism's various parts; the pattern underlying its form.
PATO:0000141.label: structure

PATO:0000140.definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's spatial location relative to other objects in the vicinity.
PATO:0000140.label: position

PATO:0001710.definition: A size quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's extension in three dimensions.
PATO:0001710.label: 3-D extent

CHEBI:25696.definition: Any organic ion with a net negative charge.
CHEBI:25696.label: organic anion

PATO:0002204.definition: Handedness where the organism exhibits no overall dominance in the use of right or left hand or foot in the performance of tasks that require one hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.
PATO:0002204.label: ambidextrous handedness

PATO:0002202.definition: Handedness where the organism preferentially uses the left hand or foot for tasks requiring the use of a single hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.
PATO:0002202.label: left handedness

PATO:0002203.definition: Handedness where the organism preferentially uses the right hand or foot for tasks requiring the use of a single hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.
PATO:0002203.label: right handedness

PATO:0001574.label: flow rate

CHEBI:17891.label: donor

CHEBI:32285.definition: A (13)C-modified compound that is urea in which the carbon is present as its (13)C isotope.
CHEBI:32285.label: ((13)C)urea

OBI:0000663.definition: A class prediction data transformation (sometimes called supervised classification) is a data transformation that has objective class prediction.
OBI:0000663.label: class prediction data transformation

ENVO:00003869.definition: An agricultural byproduct, the dry stalk of a cereal plant, after the nutrient grain or seed has been removed.
ENVO:00003869.label: straw

ENVO:01000155.definition: Environmental material derived from living organisms.
ENVO:01000155.label: organic material

ENVO:00000266.definition: Grassland used for grazing of ungulate livestock as part of a farm or ranch.
ENVO:00000266.label: pasture

ENVO:00000262.definition: A plain without trees (apart from those near rivers and lakes); it is similar to a prairie, although a prairie is generally considered as being dominated by tall grasses, while short grasses are said to be normal in the steppe. It may be semi-desert, or covered with grass or shrubs or both, depending on the season and latitude.
ENVO:00000262.label: steppe

ENVO:00000261.definition: A grassland of the tropics or subtropics with scattered trees.
ENVO:00000261.label: savanna

ENVO:00000260.definition: An area of land of low topographic relief that historically supported grasses and herbs, with few trees, and having generally a mesic (moderate or temperate) climate. Dominated by tall grasses (contrast steppe).
ENVO:00000260.label: prairie

PATO:0000952.definition: A color consisting of dark orange, red, of very low intensity.
PATO:0000952.label: brown

PATO:0000950.definition: A color between white and black colors.
PATO:0000950.label: grey

PATO:0000957.definition: An optical quality which obtains by virtue of the ability of the bearer to absorb visible light.
PATO:0000957.label: opacity

ENVO:00000063.synonyms: aquatic feature;body of water;bodies of water;waterbody
ENVO:00000063.definition: An accumulation of water of varying size.
ENVO:00000063.label: water body

PATO:0002068.definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a layered configuration.
PATO:0002068.label: stratified

OBI:0001620.definition: A measurement datum that is the measure of the latitude coordinate of a site.
OBI:0001620.label: latitude coordinate measurement datum

OBI:0001621.definition: A measurement datum that is the measure of the longitude coordinate of a site.
OBI:0001621.label: longitude coordinate measurement datum

PATO:0001791.definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being confined or restricted to multiple locations.
PATO:0001791.label: multi-localised

AGRO:00000034.definition: A fertilizer that does not contain a carbon-hydrogen linkage.
AGRO:00000034.label: inorganic fertilizer

CHEBI:48354.definition: A solvent that is composed of polar molecules. Polar solvents can dissolve ionic compounds or ionisable covalent compounds.
CHEBI:48354.label: polar solvent

AGRO:00000037.definition: An application method in which a liquid material entity is applied by aircraft to an area.
AGRO:00000037.label: aerial application

CHEBI:48356.definition: A polar solvent that is capable of acting as a hydron (proton) donor.
CHEBI:48356.label: protic solvent

ENVO:00000287.definition: An isolated hill with steep sides and a small flat top, smaller than mesas and plateaus. Buttes are formed by erosion when a cap of hard rock, usually of volcanic origin, covers a layer of softer rock that is easily worn away. This hard rock avoids erosion while the rock around it wears down.
ENVO:00000287.label: butte

ENVO:00000280.definition: A transition zone between different physiogeographic provinces that involves an elevation differential, often involving high cliffs. Most commonly a transition from one series of sedimentary rocks to another series of a different age and composition. In such cases, the escarpment usually represents the line of erosional loss of the newer rock over the older.
ENVO:00000280.label: escarpment

ENVO:00000283.definition: A long and narrow upland with steep sides.
ENVO:00000283.label: ridge

CHEBI:23004.definition: The univalent carboacyl group formed by loss of -OH from the carboxy group of carbamic acid.
CHEBI:23004.label: carbamoyl group

CHEBI:39144.definition: A molecular entity able to provide a pair of electrons and thus capable of forming a covalent bond with an electron-pair acceptor (Lewis acid), thereby producing a Lewis adduct.
CHEBI:39144.label: Lewis base

CHEBI:39141.definition: A molecular entity capable of donating a hydron to an acceptor (Bronsted base).
CHEBI:39141.label: Bronsted acid

CHEBI:39142.definition: A molecular entity capable of accepting a hydron from a donor (Bronsted acid).
CHEBI:39142.label: Bronsted base

IAO:0000027.definition: a data item is an information content entity that is intended to be a truthful statement about something (modulo, e.g., measurement precision or other systematic errors) and is constructed/acquired by a method which reliably tends to produce (approximately) truthful statements.
IAO:0000027.label: data item

UO:0000094.definition: A speed/velocity unit which is equal to the speed of an object traveling 1 meter distance in one second.
UO:0000094.label: meter per second

ENVO:01001040.definition: An environment which is determined by materials which bear significant concentrations of salts.
ENVO:01001040.label: saline environment

OBI:0000047.definition: Is a material entity that is created or changed during material processing.
OBI:0000047.label: processed material

ENVO:01001044.definition: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by soil.
ENVO:01001044.label: soil environment

PO:0006001.definition: A lateral plant organ (PO:0009008) produced by a shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148).
PO:0006001.label: phyllome

ENVO:01000804.definition: An object which is composed of one or more gravitationally bound structures that are associated with a position in space.
ENVO:01000804.label: astronomical object

ENVO:00000119.definition: A forest that has been intentionally established by human intervention.
ENVO:00000119.label: planted forest

ENVO:01000800.definition: A planet is an astronomical body orbiting a star or stellar remnant that is massive enough to be rounded by its own gravity, is not massive enough to cause thermonuclear fusion, and has cleared its neighbouring region of planetesimals.
ENVO:01000800.label: planet

OBI:0000441.definition: an objective specification to determine a specified type of information about an evaluated entity (the material entity bearing evaluant role)
OBI:0000441.label: assay objective

ENVO:00000114.definition: An area of land, usually relatively small, enclosed or otherwise and used for agricultural purposes.
ENVO:00000114.label: agricultural field

ENVO:00000117.definition: An intentional planting of a crop, on a large scale, usually for uses other than cereal production or pasture. The term is currently most often used for plantings of trees and shrubs. The term tends also to be used for plantings maintained on economic bases other than that of subsistence farming.
ENVO:00000117.label: plantation

ENVO:01000297.definition: A river where fresh water flows.
ENVO:01000297.label: freshwater river

ENVO:00000111.definition: An area with a high density of trees. A small forest may be called a wood.
ENVO:00000111.label: forest

OBI:0000444.definition: target of material addition role is a role realized by an entity into which a material is added in a material addition process
OBI:0000444.label: target of material addition role

ENVO:00000112.definition: Treeless, level, or gently rolling plains characteristic of arctic or subarctic regions, having a permanently frozen subsoil, and usually supporting low growing vegetation such as lichens, mosses, and stunted shrubs.
ENVO:00000112.label: tundra

XCO:0000000.definition: A state of being, an external or environmental factor or a treatment observed or administered prior to or concurrent with an investigative procedure such as an assessment of a morphological or physiological state or property in a single individual or sample or in a group of individuals or samples, especially a state, factor or treatment which has the potential to influence the outcome of such an assessment.
XCO:0000000.label: experimental condition

CHEBI:62488.definition: A molecular messenger in which the molecule is specifically involved in transmitting information between cells. Such molecules are released from the cell sending the signal, cross over the gap between cells by diffusion, and interact with specific receptors in another cell, triggering a response in that cell by activating a series of enzyme controlled reactions which lead to changes inside the cell.
CHEBI:62488.label: signalling molecule

PATO:0000317.definition: A color that lacks any hues as parts.
PATO:0000317.label: black

CHEBI:33405.definition: A hydracid is a compound which contains hydrogen that is not bound to oxygen, and which produces a conjugate base by loss of positive hydrogen ion(s) (hydrons).
CHEBI:33405.label: hydracid

OBI:0000707.definition: A decision tree building data transformation is a data transformation that has objective decision tree induction.
OBI:0000707.label: decision tree building data transformation

CHEBI:74783.definition: A compound that causes the contraction of body tissues, typically used to reduce bleeding from minor abrasions.
CHEBI:74783.label: astringent

CHEBI:33575.definition: A carbon oxoacid acid carrying at least one -C(=O)OH group and having the structure RC(=O)OH, where R is any any monovalent functional group. Carboxylic acids are the most common type of organic acid.
CHEBI:33575.label: carboxylic acid

BFO:0000031.definition: A continuant that is dependent on one or other independent continuant bearers. For every instance of A requires some instance of (an independent continuant type) B but which instance of B serves can change from time to time.
BFO:0000031.label: generically dependent continuant

AGRO:00000394.definition: A disk harrow with disc blades arranged into four sections.
AGRO:00000394.label: tandem disc harrow

AGRO:00000427.definition: Grazing management system developped by Allan Savory. The system is based on a rotational grazing system but doing so at high densities for short intervals. Livestock is used as a tool to increase soil fertility and plant life. Incorporating plant organic matter and manure into the soil promotes the recycling of nutrients.
AGRO:00000427.label: holistic planned grazing

AGRO:00000396.definition: A sowing device that positions seeds in the soil and then covers them. The seed drill sows the seeds at equal distances and proper depth, ensuring that the seeds get covered with soil.
AGRO:00000396.label: seed drill

AGRO:00000397.definition: A seeding implement that consists of a seed drum, main shaft, ground wheel, floats, and handle. Joining smaller ends of frustum of cones makes the seed drum.
AGRO:00000397.label: drum seeder

AGRO:00000390.definition: An agricultural field that is set aside for a period of time before it is cultivated again; or an agricultral field that is under permanent crops, meadows or pastures and that is not being used for such purposes for a period of at least one year.
AGRO:00000390.label: fallow land

AGRO:00000391.definition:
Strips of land along the borders of crop fields. It also include vegetative strips adjacent
to roads, paths, railways, hedgerows and forest boundaries.
AGRO:00000391.label: field margin

AGRO:00000392.definition: Tool for loosening compacted soil layers 12 to 16 inches (30 to 40 cm) deep and still maintain high surface residue levels.
AGRO:00000392.label: paraplough

AGRO:00000393.definition: Tillage tool that stirs and pulverizes the soil, either before planting (to aerate the soil and prepare a smooth, loose seedbed) or after the crop has begun growing (to kill weeds—controlled disturbance of the topsoil close to the crop plants kills the surrounding weeds by uprooting them, burying their leaves to disrupt their photosynthesis, or a combination of both). Cultivator is designed to disturb the soil in careful patterns, sparing the crop plants but disrupting the weeds. Cultivator teeth work near the surface.
AGRO:00000393.label: cultivator

CHEBI:75787.definition: Any metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in prokaryotes, the taxon that include members of domains such as the bacteria and archaea.
CHEBI:75787.label: prokaryotic metabolite

AGRO:00000398.definition: An agricultural hand tool ade of a blade set to an handle and used to shape the soil, control weeds, clear soil, and harvest root crops.
AGRO:00000398.label: hoe

AGRO:00000399.definition:
A seed drill that consists of a seed box attached to the mainframe of a hand wheel hoe. A fluted roller assembly is provided at the bottom of the seed box. Fluted roller is rotated with the help of
chain and sprockets from the ground wheel.
AGRO:00000399.label: manual oilseed drill

AGRO:00000428.definition: A grazing management method that involves moving livestock at least daily between small paddocks, sized to match the number of grazing animals, and split by fence. The goal is for every plant in the grazing cell to be either eaten or walked on and trampled. Grass in each paddock then rests for 60-120 days or more.
AGRO:00000428.label: mob grazing

PATO:0000133.definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's placement which is defined by the angle between the bearer and an axis, or the angle between the bearer and another object.
PATO:0000133.label: orientation

PO:0025082.definition: A shoot system (PO:0009006) in the sporophytic phase that has as part at least one sporangium (PO:0025094).
PO:0025082.label: reproductive shoot system

OBI:0002357.definition: A performance status value specification designed by the Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group to assess disease progression and its affect on the daily living abilities of the patient.
OBI:0002357.label: Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group score value specification

OBI:0002356.definition: A categorical value specification that is an assessment of a participant's performance status (general well-being and activities of daily life).
OBI:0002356.label: performance status value specification

CHEBI:51422.definition: Any organic substituent group, regardless of functional type, having two free valences at carbon atom(s).
CHEBI:51422.label: organodiyl group

UO:0000111.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the work done by a certain force (gravitational, electric, magnetic, force of inertia, etc).
UO:0000111.label: energy unit

PATO:0000048.definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resistance to pressure, being broken, or pierced
PATO:0000048.label: hardness

PATO:0000044.definition: A physical quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of the number of the bearer's repetitive actions in a particular time.
PATO:0000044.label: frequency

PATO:0001548.definition: A physical quality inhering in an entity exhibiting the physical characteristics of an amorphous (non-crystalline) form of matter between a gas and a solid that has a definite volume, but no definite shape.
PATO:0001548.label: quality of a liquid

AGRO:00000274.definition: Protocol used to determine the content of organic nitrogen in environmental material.
AGRO:00000274.label: determination of organic nitrogen in environmental material protocol

PATO:0000040.definition: A quality that is the extent of space between two entities.
PATO:0000040.label: distance

AGRO:00000140.definition: An implement designed to inject slurry into the soil.
AGRO:00000140.label: slurry injector

CHEBI:83039.definition: An animal metabolite produced by arthropods such as crabs, lobsters, crayfish, shrimps and krill.
CHEBI:83039.label: crustacean metabolite

ENVO:00000476.definition: An opening of a lake into its shore.
ENVO:00000476.label: lake inlet

ENVO:00000475.definition: An opening of the sea into the land, or of a lake into its shore.
ENVO:00000475.label: inlet

CHEBI:22563.definition: A monoatomic or polyatomic species having one or more elementary charges of the electron.
CHEBI:22563.label: anion

CHEBI:78433.definition: A substance used in a thermodynamic heat pump cycle or refrigeration cycle that undergoes a phase change from a gas to a liquid and back. Refrigerants are used in air-conditioning systems and freezers or refrigerators and are assigned a "R" number (by ASHRAE - formerly the American Society of Heating, Refrigerating and Air Conditioning Engineers), which is determined systematically according to their molecular structure.
CHEBI:78433.label: refrigerant

ENVO:00000077.synonyms: dairy;grazing allotment;nursery;pastoral site;stockyard;irrigated field;corral;grange;bailing station;cattle dipping tank;feedlot;barn;sheepfold
ENVO:00000077.label: agricultural feature

OBI:0000704.definition: A decision tree induction objective is a data transformation objective in which a tree-like graph of edges and nodes is created and from which the selection of each branch requires that some type of logical decision is made.
OBI:0000704.label: decision tree induction objective

ENVO:00000070.definition: A feature that has been constructed by deliberate human effort.
ENVO:00000070.label: construction

ENVO:00000078.definition: A tract of crop or grazing land, as well as the group of buildings with and often surrounding a farmhouse, including barns, sheds, and other outbuildings, used for agricultural production.
ENVO:00000078.label: farm

CHEBI:32588.definition: A metal chloride salt with a K(+) counterion.
CHEBI:32588.label: potassium chloride

ENVO:00000297.definition: A flooded parcel of arable land used for growing rice and other semiaquatic crops.
ENVO:00000297.label: paddy field

ENVO:00000291.definition: An extent or area of land where surface water from rain and melting snow or ice converges to a single point at lower elevation, usually the exit of the basin, where the waters join another waterbody.
ENVO:00000291.label: drainage basin

ENVO:01000231.definition: Lava is a mixture of molten or semi-molten rock, volatiles, and solids which has extruded beyond a planetary crust.
ENVO:01000231.label: lava

ENVO:01000230.definition: An environmental condition in which annual precipitation is less than half of annual potential evapotranspiration.
ENVO:01000230.label: arid

OBI:0200111.definition: An planned process that creates images, diagrams or animations from the input data.
OBI:0200111.label: data visualization

OBI:0000679.definition: A  data item that is produced as the output of an averaging data transformation and represents the average value of the input data.
OBI:0000679.label: average value

ENVO:02500027.definition: An environmental process which is driven by the action of humans.
ENVO:02500027.label: anthropogenic environmental process

ENVO:02500028.definition: An action of exogenic processes (such as water flow or wind) which remove soil and rock from one location on the Earth's crust, then transport it to another location where it is deposited.
ENVO:02500028.label: erosion

OBI:0000674.definition: A data item that is produced as the output of a center calculation data transformation and represents the center value of the input data.
OBI:0000674.label: center value

OGMS:0000031.definition: A disposition (i) to undergo pathological processes that (ii) exists in an organism because of one or more disorders in that organism.
OGMS:0000031.label: disease

CHEBI:63038.definition: The ammonium salt of nitric acid.
CHEBI:63038.label: ammonium nitrate

UO:0000022.definition: A mass unit which is equal to one thousandth of a gram or 10^[-3] g.
UO:0000022.label: milligram

CHEBI:28616.definition: A one-carbon compound that is ammonia in which one of the hydrogens is replaced by a carboxy group. Although carbamic acid derivatives are common, carbamic acid itself has never been synthesised.
CHEBI:28616.label: carbamic acid

UO:0000021.definition: A mass unit which is equal to one thousandth of a kilogram or 10^[-3] kg.
UO:0000021.label: gram

UO:0000027.definition: A temperature unit which is equal to one kelvin degree. However, they have their zeros at different points. The centigrade scale has its zero at 273.15 K.
UO:0000027.label: degree Celsius

ENVO:01001052.definition: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by an aerosol.
ENVO:01001052.label: aerosol environment

ENVO:01001053.definition: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by a saline aerosol.
ENVO:01001053.label: saline aerosol environment

ENVO:01001057.definition: An environmental system determined by part of a living or dead plant, or a whole small plant.
ENVO:01001057.label: environment associated with a plant part or small plant

ENVO:01001054.definition: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by an aerosol with a low concentration of dissolved solutes.
ENVO:01001054.label: non-saline aerosol environment

ENVO:01001055.definition: An environmental system determined by part of a living or dead animal, or a whole small animal.
ENVO:01001055.label: environment associated with an animal part or small animal

ENVO:00000108.definition: A habitat of rolling or flat terrain where grasses predominate. Typically, what is called a meadow has more biodiversity than a grassland as the former contains not only grasses but a significant variety of annual, biennial and perennial plants.
ENVO:00000108.label: meadow

ENVO:00000109.definition: Land having a cover of trees, shrubs, or both.
ENVO:00000109.label: woodland

OBI:0000456.definition: an objective specifiction that creates an specific output object from input materials.
OBI:0000456.label: material transformation objective

ENVO:00010483.definition: A portion of environmental material is a fiat object which forms the medium or part of the medium of an environmental system.
ENVO:00010483.label: environmental material

ENVO:01000839.definition: Combustion or burning is a high-temperature exothermic redox chemical reaction between a fuel and an oxidant that produces oxidized, often gaseous products, in a mixture termed as smoke.
ENVO:01000839.label: combustion process

OBI:0000450.definition: A regulatory agency is a organization that has responsibility over or for  the legislation (acts and regulations) for a given sector of the government.
OBI:0000450.label: regulatory agency

PO:0025530.definition: A shoot system development stage (PO:0025527) that has as primary participant a reproductive shoot system (PO:0025082).
PO:0025530.label: reproductive shoot system development stage

PO:0025023.definition: A collective plant organ structure (PO:0025007) that consists of two or more phyllomes (PO:0006001) originating from the same node or from one or more adjacent nodes with compressed shoot internodes (PO:0005005).
PO:0025023.label: collective phyllome structure

PO:0006210.definition: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that is the outer layer of an apical meristem (PO:0020144), or the outer layer of a plant embryo proper (PO:0000001), and gives rise to a portion of epidermis (PO:0005679).
PO:0006210.label: protoderm

CHEBI:33692.definition: Hydrides are chemical compounds of hydrogen with other chemical elements.
CHEBI:33692.label: hydrides

IAO:0000225.definition: The reason for which a term has been deprecated. The allowed values come from an enumerated list of predefined terms. See the specification of these instances for more detailed definitions of each enumerated value.
IAO:0000225.label: obsolescence reason specification

CHEBI:36339.definition: Baryon is a fermion that does experience the strong force (strong interaction). The term is derived from the Greek betaalpharhoupsilonsigma (heavy).
CHEBI:36339.label: baryon

CHEBI:36338.definition: Lepton is a fermion that does not experience the strong force (strong interaction). The term is derived from the Greek lambdaepsilonpitauomicronsigma (small, thin).
CHEBI:36338.label: lepton

ENVO:00003030.definition: A fermented, high-moisture forage that can be fed to ruminants.
ENVO:00003030.label: silage

AGRO:00000097.definition: A mulch where pine needles are used to cover soil surface.
AGRO:00000097.label: pine needles mulch

AGRO:00000096.definition: A mulch where lawn waste resulting from mowing are used to cover the soil surface.
AGRO:00000096.label: grass clippings mulch

AGRO:00000095.definition: A mulch where shredded or entire piece of paper or newspaper cover the soil surface.
AGRO:00000095.label: paper mulch

AGRO:00000094.definition: A mulch where textile material is used to covert the soil surface. The fabric itself can be made from synthetic or organic materials, sometimes from recycled sources.
AGRO:00000094.label: landscape fabric

AGRO:00000093.definition: A mulch where plastic sheet is used to cover soil surface. Plants grow through slits or holes in thin plastic sheeting.
AGRO:00000093.label: plastic mulch

AGRO:00000091.definition: A compost that contains the residual compost waste generated by mushroom production. It  generally consists of a combination of wheat straw, dried blood, horse manure and ground chalk, composted together.
AGRO:00000091.label: spent mushroom compost

AGRO:00000090.definition: An agricultural environmental material that contains ground dry alfalfa.
AGRO:00000090.label: alfalfa meal

AGRO:00000099.definition: A mulch where foil is used to cover soil surface.
AGRO:00000099.label: aluminum mulch

AGRO:00000098.definition: A mulch where straw is used to cover soil surface.
AGRO:00000098.label: straw mulch

AGRO:00000255.definition: Measurement protocol in which the depth into the soil of an agricultural process is measured.
AGRO:00000255.label: agricultural process depth measurement protocol

AGRO:00000257.definition: Measure the length of the implement that goes into the soil to realize the agricultural process to knoe the depth of the agricultural process. For exemple, measure the length of the tool blade used for tillage to evaluate tillage depth.
AGRO:00000257.label: implement lenght measurement protocol

AGRO:00000256.definition: Use of a penometer to measure the depth of the agricultural process.

CHEBI:26836.synonyms: sulfuric acid;tetraoxosulfuric acid;Sulfuric acid;hydrogen tetraoxosulfate(VI);dihydroxidodioxidosulfur;hydrogen tetraoxosulfate(2-);dihydrogen tetraoxosulfate
CHEBI:26836.definition: A sulfur oxoacid that consits of two oxo and two hydroxy groups joined covalently to a central sulfur atom.
CHEBI:26836.label: sulfuric acid

CHEBI:18367.definition: A phosphate ion that is the conjugate base of hydrogenphosphate.
CHEBI:18367.label: phosphate(3-)

AGRO:00000208.definition: A mechanical pest control process in which the soil is covered with a layer of clear or black plastic. The plastic that is covering the ground traps heat energy from the sun and raises the temperature of the soil killing pest.
AGRO:00000208.label: soil solarization treatment

AGRO:00000209.definition: A mechanical pest control process in which pest or area with pest are directly burned and flamed.
AGRO:00000209.label: fire treatment

AGRO:00000202.definition: An area density quality which inheres in seeds by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of the seeds sown on a given surface area.
AGRO:00000202.label: seeding area density

OBI:0000202.definition: A role borne by an entity and that is realized in a process that is part of an investigation in which an objective is achieved. These processes include, among others: planning, overseeing, funding, reviewing.
OBI:0000202.label: investigation agent role

AGRO:00000200.definition: An area density quality which inheres in fertilizer by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of fertilizer applied in a given surface area.
AGRO:00000200.label: fertilizer area density

AGRO:00000201.definition: An area density quality which inheres in potassium by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of potassium applied in a given surface area.
AGRO:00000201.label: potassium area density

AGRO:00000206.definition: A pest control process in which extremely cold temperature are used to kill pest.
AGRO:00000206.label: cold treatment

AGRO:00000207.definition: A mechanical pest control process in which the area being treated against pest is saturated with water at a depth of 15 to 30 cm for a period of 3 to 8 weeks.
AGRO:00000207.label: flood treatment

AGRO:00000204.definition: A pest control process in wich extremely hot temperature are used to kill pest.
AGRO:00000204.label: heat treatment

AGRO:00000205.definition: An area density quality which inheres in plant reproductive material by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of plant reproductive material planted in a given surface area.
AGRO:00000205.label: plant reproductive material area density

UO:0000217.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the work done per unit charge as a charge is moved between two points in an electric field.
UO:0000217.label: electric potential difference unit

UO:0000218.definition: An electric potential difference unit which is equal to the work per unit charge. One volt is the potential difference required to move one coulomb of charge between two points in a circuit while using one joule of energy.
UO:0000218.label: volt

CHEBI:35406.definition: An oxoanion is an anion derived from an oxoacid by loss of hydron(s) bound to oxygen.
CHEBI:35406.label: oxoanion

RO:0002534.definition: Any entity that can be divided into parts such that each part is an atomical unit of a sequence
RO:0002534.label: sequence bearer

RO:0002533.definition: Any individual unit of a collection of like units arranged in a linear order
RO:0002533.label: sequence atomic unit

RO:0002532.definition: Any entity that is ordered in discrete units along a linear axis.
RO:0002532.label: sequentially ordered entity

AGRO:00000336.definition: A lattice design in which the number of treatment must be a perfect square. Blocks per replicate and plots per block are equal, and are the square root of the number of treatments.
AGRO:00000336.label: square lattice design

AGRO:00000337.definition: A lattice design that is a resolvable incomplete block design where the number of treatments or block size does not meet the strict requirements for one of the lattice designs. Also the number of entries is a multiple of block size.
AGRO:00000337.label: alpha lattice design

AGRO:00000335.definition: An experimental design in which basic farming practices are compared using demonstration strips on a farm field. Usually the comparison is between two to four treatments, up to a maximum of 10 and each treatment is included only once.
AGRO:00000335.label: demonstration strip design

AGRO:00000332.definition: An experimental design in which the treatments are assigned completely at random so that each experimental unit has the same chance of receiving any one treatment. Any difference among experimental units receiving the same treatment is considered as experimental error. Hence, it is appropriate only for experiments with homogeneous experimental units, such as laboratory experiments, where environmental effects are relatively easy to control.
AGRO:00000332.label: completely randomized design

AGRO:00000333.definition: An experimental design in which the blocks should be composed of plots that are as homogeneous as possible. Further, blocks in the same replication should be as near as possible to maximize the variation among replication. These incomplete blocks are combined into groups that form separate, complete replications.
AGRO:00000333.label: lattice design

AGRO:00000330.definition:
An experimental design in which the desired precision for measuring the interaction effect between the two factors is higher than that for measuring the main effect of either one of  the two factors. This is accomplished with the use of three plot sizes : 
1. Vertical strip plot for the first factor – vertical factor 
2. Horizontal strip plot for the second factor – horizontal factor 
3. Interaction plot for the interaction between 2 factors
AGRO:00000330.label: strip plot design

AGRO:00000331.definition: An experimental design in which two or more factors, each with discrete possible values or "levels", and whose experimental units take on all possible combinations of these levels across all such factors. That is, the design provides information on the average effect of the individual factors as well as the interaction between these two factors.
AGRO:00000331.label: factorial design

AGRO:00000448.definition: Amount of nutrient in the crop as a ratio of the amount applied or available.
AGRO:00000448.label: nitrogen recovery efficiency

AGRO:00000449.definition: Calculate the amount of nitrogen in the crop as a ratio of the amount of nitrogen applied or available.
AGRO:00000449.label: nitrogen recovery efficiency measurement protocol

AGRO:00000338.definition: The landform refers to the shape of the land surface in the area in which the agronomic trial site is located.
AGRO:00000338.label: higher-level landform

AGRO:00000339.definition: Description of the geomorphology of the immediate surroundings of the experimental site.
AGRO:00000339.label: agronomic land element

CHEBI:64641.definition: An inorganic cation with a valency of two.
CHEBI:64641.label: divalent inorganic cation

PATO:0001464.definition: A quality that is equal to the potential energy per unit charge associated with a static (time-invariant) electric field, also called the electrostatic potential.
PATO:0001464.label: electric potential

CHEBI:33246.definition: Any substituent group which does not contain carbon.
CHEBI:33246.label: inorganic group

CHEBI:33247.definition: Any substituent group or skeleton containing carbon.
CHEBI:33247.label: organic group

PATO:0001264.definition: A color consisting of yellow hue and high brightness.
PATO:0001264.label: light yellow

CHEBI:33249.definition: Any organic substituent group, regardless of functional type, having one free valence at a carbon atom.
CHEBI:33249.label: organyl group

CHEBI:76946.definition: Any eukaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in fungi, the kingdom that includes microorganisms such as the yeasts and moulds.
CHEBI:76946.label: fungal metabolite

AGRO:00000022.definition: A pest control process in which organisms are employed to manage unwanted organisms.
AGRO:00000022.label: biological pest control process

AGRO:00000023.definition: A planned process in which unwanted organisms are controlled.
AGRO:00000023.label: pest control process

AGRO:00000020.definition: A land levelling process in which a laser guided equipement is used to shape land surface.
AGRO:00000020.label: laser land levelling process

AGRO:00000021.definition: A pest control process in which physical means such as barriers, traps and handpicking, or physical conditions like high temperature, are used to control unwanted organisms.
AGRO:00000021.label: mechanical pest control process

AGRO:00000026.definition: A planned process in which the soil is left undisturbed apart from where the seeds or planting material are placed.
AGRO:00000026.label: no-till

AGRO:00000027.definition: A planned process in which selected parts of the plant are removed. The practice entails targeted removal of diseased, damaged, dead, non-productive, structurally unsound, or otherwise unwanted tissue from plants. This is done in order to shape the plant or tree, improve plant or tree health, reduce the risk from falling branches, prepare nursery specimens for transplanting, and increase the yield or quality of harvested products.
AGRO:00000027.label: pruning process

AGRO:00000024.definition: A pest control process in which chemical is used to manage unwanted organisms.
AGRO:00000024.label: chemical pest control process

AGRO:00000025.definition: A planned process in which the useful part or parts of the plant are gathered.
AGRO:00000025.label: harvesting process

AGRO:00000028.definition: A tillage process in which saturated or near-saturated soil are worked into soft structureless mud, mainly for paddy rice production.
AGRO:00000028.label: puddling process

AGRO:00000029.definition: A conservation tillage process in which non-inversion tillage tools that partially incorporate surface organic material are used on the entire surface of the field.
AGRO:00000029.label: mulch-till

ENVO:01000799.definition: An object which is naturally occuring, bound together by gravitational or electromagnetic forces, and surrounded by space.
ENVO:01000799.label: astronomical body

ENVO:01000792.definition: A process whereby a large volume of gas moves due to a disequilibrium of physical forces.
ENVO:01000792.label: mass gaseous flow

ENVO:01000790.definition: A flame which is produced by the combustion of hydrocarbon fuel.
ENVO:01000790.label: hydrocarbon flame

CHEBI:36962.definition: An organochalcogen compound is a compound containing at least one carbon-chalcogen bond.
CHEBI:36962.label: organochalcogen compound

ENVO:01000797.definition: A material entity which is composed of one or more chemical entities and has neither independent shape nor volume but tends to expand indefinitely.
ENVO:01000797.label: gaseous environmental material

CHEBI:43474.definition: A phosphate ion that is the conjugate base of dihydrogenphosphate.
CHEBI:43474.label: hydrogenphosphate

CHEBI:33300.definition: Any p-block element atom that is in group 15 of the periodic table: nitrogen, phosphorus, arsenic, antimony and bismuth.
CHEBI:33300.label: pnictogen

CHEBI:33303.definition: Any p-block element belonging to the group 16 family of the periodic table.
CHEBI:33303.label: chalcogen

CHEBI:33302.definition: A p-block molecular entity containing any pnictogen.
CHEBI:33302.label: pnictogen molecular entity

CHEBI:33304.definition: Any p-block molecular entity containing a chalcogen.
CHEBI:33304.label: chalcogen molecular entity

PATO:0000025.definition: A single physical entity inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's quantities or relative ratios of subparts.
PATO:0000025.label: composition

PATO:0002201.definition: A behavioral quality inhering ina bearer by virtue of the bearer's unequal distribution of fine motor skill between its left and right hands or feet.
PATO:0002201.label: handedness

OBI:0002205.definition: A categorical value specification that is a histologic grade assigned to a tumor slide specimen according to the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) 7th Edition grading system.
OBI:0002205.label: histologic grade according to AJCC 7th edition

AGRO:00000158.definition: An area density quality which inheres in nitrogen by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of nitrogen applied in a given surface area.
AGRO:00000158.label: nitrogen area density

AGRO:00000156.definition: A site which is located between two rows of crop plants.
AGRO:00000156.label: interrow

AGRO:00000155.definition: two or more crop plants planted in a line.
AGRO:00000155.label: row

AGRO:00000152.definition: An area density quality which inheres in liming material by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of liming material applied on a given surface area.
AGRO:00000152.label: liming material area density
